Political analyst, Sandile Swana says South Africa has enough brain power and technical know-how to resolve problems at Eskom. His comment come after President Cyril Ramaphosa vowed this weekend to place the country’s power crisis, unemployment and land redistribution at the top of the African National Congress’ (ANC) list of priorities for 2020. Ramaphosa and ANC members met in Kimberley on Saturday to celebrate the party’s 108th anniversary. He  said government will not allow Eskom to fail and promised to restore the power utility. Speaking on Morning Live, Swana says the country’s most experience engineers are not put on the board of Eskom and employed as senior engineers. Click below to watch the full interview: